transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi. Hey, I was, uh, shipped the wrong product. I ordered Scorblue, and what I got was generics of that.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me see my phone again. So I don't know how that happened.

Speaker 2: Pardon me?

Speaker 1: I'm trying to put your information up with your phone number, and I'll go ahead and see what's going on.

Speaker 2: Is this Mr. White I'm talking to?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir, it is.

Speaker 2: All right, Mr. White, let me go ahead and see what's going on.

Speaker 1: All right, okay, I'm looking at you.

Speaker 2: You ordered the Viagra.

Speaker 1: It looks like you got the 100 milligrams, the 40.

Speaker 2: Did you go online to place your order?

Speaker 1: I'm just curious.

Speaker 2: Is that how you did your order when you did it?

Speaker 1: Yes, but I ordered Viagra Scorblue, the AGB, whatever that is.

Speaker 2: I got you.

Speaker 1: We're going to take care of that for you.

Speaker 2: That seems to be – that's happened a few times.

Speaker 1: When an individual orders online, they don't get the actual AGB.

Speaker 2: They get the regular Viagra, but not a problem.

Speaker 1: We're going to get that corrected for you right now.

Speaker 2: Bear with me one second.

Speaker 1: I see you got the 40.

Speaker 2: Let me explain to you the difference on that one.

Speaker 1: It's going to look very similar because the pills are made from the same

Speaker 2: Pfizer lab in France.

Speaker 1: The only difference is it's going to be a white-shaped diamond

Speaker 2: with the number 100 on the back of it.

Speaker 1: That's how you can tell the difference that it's the AGB.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll get that sent out to you.

Speaker 1: But when it comes in the bottle, does it say AGB or does it –

Speaker 2: Your prescription bottle is going to look the same

Speaker 1: because that is the prescription of the –

Speaker 2: But what is it going to say?

Speaker 1: Your pill is going to have the 100 on it.

Speaker 2: That's what it's going to say because it's pilled by Viagra 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: I'm just telling you, it's going to say exactly what it says on your bottle

Speaker 2: that you received, but it's going to be a different pill.

Speaker 1: It's not going to say AGB on the bottle?

Speaker 2: No, it's not going to say that on the bottle.

Speaker 1: It's going to be in the bottle.

Speaker 2: And the difference is going to be the pill is going to have the 100.

Speaker 1: It's going to look almost exactly the same as the generic Viagra,

Speaker 2: but it has a 100 on the back, and that's how you can tell the difference.

Speaker 1: And that's why a lot of times it's a mix-up at the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: And what does the bottle say?

Speaker 1: Your bottle is going to have the same prescription on it,

Speaker 2: the same prescription that you have on what you received

Speaker 1: because it's 100 milligrams of Viagra, but it's the AGB.

Speaker 2: The actual pill is going to have the number 100 on it.

Speaker 1: Okay, I got it.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: When are you going to ship that out?

Speaker 1: I'm going to send it to the pharmacy to go out today,

Speaker 2: and no charge because I should have got the first time.

Speaker 1: All right?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thanks very much, sir.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
